        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 2:51PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 250 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of West Valley, or 11 miles west of Anaconda, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar &amp; satellite indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deer Lodge, Anaconda, Warm Springs, Galen, Garrison, West Valley,
Avon, Racetrack, Lost Creek, Opportunity, Blossburg, Georgetown, and
Elliston.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 90 between mile markers 170 and 206.
Highway 12 Garrison to MacDonald Pass between mile markers 0 and 26.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
